4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING FOR LOCAL LAW ENFORCEMENT SERVICE
5 REGULATIONS FOR CITIES AND TOWNS; PROVIDING LOCAL LAW ENFORCEMENT SERVICE FEE
6 GUIDELINES; SUPERSEDING THE UNFUNDED MANDATE LAWS; PROVIDING A DEFINITION; AND
7 AMENDING SECTION 7-32-4101, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 7-32-4101, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "7-32-4101. Police department authorized and required -- requirements for county sheriff
13 services -- charge for local law enforcement services -- dispute resolution -- definition. (1) Unless
14 otherwise provided in subsection (2), There there shall must be in every city and town of this state a police
15 department which shall that must be organized, managed, and controlled as provided in this part.
16 (2) A third-class city or a town of this state may enter into a contract or interlocal agreement, in
17 whole or in part, with a state-recognized local law enforcement agency within the third-class city or town's
18 county to satisfy the requirement in subsection (1).
19 (3) The sheriff of the county where a city or town is located shall provide law enforcement services,
20 as provided by law, within that city or town if that city or town does not maintain a police department and does
21 not have an agreement as provided in subsection (2). A city or town receiving law enforcement services by the
22 county sheriff as provided in this subsection (3) is required to pay for the law enforcement services.
23 (4) If a city or town and the sheriff required to provide law enforcement services to the city or town,
24 as provided in subsection (3), are unable to come to an agreement as to the price to pay for law enforcement
25 services, the city or town or the sheriff shall request the local government center at Montana state university to
26 moderate a discussion between the local governing body of the city or town and the sheriff after 30 days of the
27 municipality not having law enforcement services. If an agreement cannot be made within 30 days of the
28 moderated meeting as to the price to pay for law enforcement services provided in subsection (3), the parties
